I was looking for a heated outdoor sushi place and again pops up Ako. I met with 2 of my friends who were in Manhattan and asked them to come to Williamsburg for better parking and food. They got to Ako before me.  I found plenty of metered parking on the street and when I entered, all the chairs inside were stacked up. No indoor dining. Went all the way to the back and all sections back there were sectioned off. They do a good job separating everyone who wants to dine there. Since I have been here before,  I ordered the Chicken Karaage....this is so fantastic.  We loved it so much, we ordered 3 throughout the time we spent. Also had the same male waiter as I did last time. He takes care of us. He seemed to smile when we asked to do the Sake Bomb! We had 3 of those also!! My buddy ordered the big bowl of meat soup with noodles, and it hit the spot. They also give you a bottle of powdered hot pepper so you can add your own heat. The pan seared gyoza also hit the spot. The place started filling up but because of the dividers, its not easy to see the other people there. Its a good thing due to this covid. Ako is a good place to go with good prices and a friendly staff. I would return here without a problem.

We ordered food for 2 people and they gave us 1 soy sauce, 1 set of chopsticks, literally 1 napkin, and spicy salmon roll were supposed to be chopped. The experience wasn’t up to par with other places in the area.

Just moved to Williamsburg a month ago and needed to find a new Japanese spot. This place looked good so a friend and I gave it a try.
